I will look like the worst kind of tyrant if I attack him.

216
00:12:12,562 --> 00:12:16,403
波斯卡认为我应该接受休战
Posca here thinks I should accept the truce.

217
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:18,674
 缔造和平  那能够换来什么？
 Make peace.  In exchange for what?

218
00:12:18,744 --> 00:12:20,364
和平本身就是回报
 Peace is it's own reward.  Snivelry.

219
00:12:20,394 --> 00:12:21,864
妇人之仁
The ram has touched the wall. No mercy.

220
00:12:22,334 --> 00:12:24,925
撞锤已经贴在城墙外面了，不能仁慈

221
00:12:24,955 --> 00:12:27,866
庞贝身边没有军队，但是有元老院
Pompey has no great army, but he has the Senate with him.

222
00:12:27,866 --> 00:12:29,236
他带有合法性
 He has legitimacy.  In Rome they are the Senate.

223
00:12:29,246 --> 00:12:30,986
他们在罗马才是元老院

224
00:12:31,236 --> 00:12:33,717
走出了城墙他们不过是300个没有用的老头儿
Beyond the walls they are just 300 old men.

225
00:12:33,757 --> 00:12:36,148
你说的有道理，安东尼，但是别人会认同波斯卡的看法，
As you say, Antony, but others will agree with Posca.

226
00:12:36,538 --> 00:12:38,638
不过他们已经公开向我投降了
They have made this shameful surrender public.

227
00:12:38,678 --> 00:12:40,769
整个意大利都会知道
It will be read all over ltaly.

228
00:12:40,779 --> 00:12:43,709
如果我不是暴君
If I am not a tyrant,

229
00:12:43,709 --> 00:12:45,090
如果我要的只是合法性
if I merely seek legitimacy,

230
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:48,060
为什么不能接受他们的条款呢？
why would I not accept such favorable terms?

231
00:12:49,211 --> 00:12:52,651
他拒绝与我们会晤
He refuses to meet us...

232
00:12:53,051 --> 00:12:55,252
单独的会晤？
in person?

233
00:12:59,153 --> 00:13:02,214
很好，这个简单
very good. Simple.

234
00:13:02,254 --> 00:13:04,184
民众会明白这么一个理由
Hoi polloi can understand a reason like that.

235
00:13:04,394 --> 00:13:07,015
他拒绝见我
He refuses to meet me face to face.

236
00:13:07,015 --> 00:13:08,195
拒绝面对面地见我
Man to man.

237
00:13:09,015 --> 00:13:11,186
拒绝会晤
He refuses to meet me.

238
00:13:11,386 --> 00:13:13,616
对，就是这个了
Right, that's it.

239
00:13:14,016 --> 00:13:15,236
决不休战，
No truce. Let's be after them.

240
00:13:15,386 --> 00:13:16,847
我们这就追他
Patience.

241
00:13:17,087 --> 00:13:18,587
耐心点

242
00:13:19,888 --> 00:13:21,528
他跑不了的
He's well caught.

243
00:13:22,958 --> 00:13:24,989
等时机成熟了我们再出发
We'll leave when the time is right.

244
00:13:28,329 --> 00:13:29,860
什么时候？
When?

245
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:32,870
时机成熟之时
When the time is right.

246
00:13:33,461 --> 00:13:35,581
我们早就应该离开罗马了
But we should have left Rome long ago.

247
00:13:35,701 --> 00:13:37,391
苹果熟了早该摘了
The apple is ripe for the plucking,

248
00:13:37,401 --> 00:13:40,042
而我们却呆坐着什么都不干？
and we just sit here doing nothing?

249
00:13:41,662 --> 00:13:43,503
庞贝不是苹果
Pompey is not an apple

250
00:13:44,363 --> 00:13:46,664
我也不是农夫
and I am not a farmer.

251
00:13:47,364 --> 00:13:48,914
传守卫
Call for my guard.

252
00:14:09,309 --> 00:14:11,669
百夫长卢休斯·乌瑞纳斯
First Spear Centurion Lucius Vorenus.

253
00:14:11,689 --> 00:14:13,280
等你回来等了好久
I have been looking for your return.

254
00:14:13,430 --> 00:14:14,740
我退役了，公民
I'm no longer in the army, citizen.

255
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,230
我来把存货给卖了
I've come to sell my stock.

256
00:14:16,890 --> 00:14:18,591
啊，嗯…
Ah,well...

257
00:14:38,865 --> 00:14:41,416
脱水腹泻，我无能为力
Black blood flux. Nothing to be done.

258
00:14:42,136 --> 00:14:43,616
腹泻？
 Flux?  I kept 'em here despite the stink

259
00:14:43,826 --> 00:14:45,577
虽然臭不可当，但是我可是还把他们留着
so you'd know I'd done you nothing dodgy.

260
00:14:45,707 --> 00:14:47,517
所以我没有耍什么花招

261
00:14:48,177 --> 00:14:49,348
也不是谁的错
Nobody to blame.

262
00:14:50,308 --> 00:14:52,829
还好你还剩下一个
Fortune left you one at least.

263
00:14:52,979 --> 00:14:54,579
就是那个幸运的孩子
 Auspicious boy that is.  How much will he fetch?

264
00:14:54,829 --> 00:14:57,290
那能换多少钱？

265
00:14:57,340 --> 00:15:00,130
哦，一大笔钱
Oh, a respectable price.

266
00:15:00,230 --> 00:15:02,501
足够把喂养费还了还有剩下的
More than enough to pay the feed bill.

267
00:15:03,081 --> 00:15:04,651
喂养费？
 Feed bill?  They didn't starve to death.

268
00:15:04,751 --> 00:15:06,102
他们可没有饿死

269
00:15:13,013 --> 00:15:14,333
快走！
Move!

270
00:15:23,555 --> 00:15:24,426
什么都没了？
 Nothing?  Not nothing. The boy will fetch

271
00:15:24,426 --> 00:15:25,886
不是一无所有，
 a good price when he's healthy.  What's that?

272
00:15:25,886 --> 00:15:27,306
这小孩子健康起来后能卖个好价钱
Your father brought him back from Gaul. What will we do till then?

273
00:15:27,306 --> 00:15:29,257
 那是什么？  你爸爸把他从高卢带回来的，

274
00:15:29,307 --> 00:15:30,497
在那之前我们能怎么样？
To keep?

275
00:15:30,607 --> 00:15:33,088
 养着他？  等他有点血色我们就把他卖了
We're selling him as soon as he gets some color.

276
00:15:33,088 --> 00:15:34,108
那卖了之后呢？
 What will we do after that?  What's his name?

277
00:15:34,108 --> 00:15:36,278
 他叫什么名字？ 没有名字
He hasn't got one!

278
00:15:36,278 --> 00:15:38,809
我把他叫做卢比奥，那是我死去的鸽子的名字
We'll call him Rubio after my pigeon that died.

279
00:15:38,809 --> 00:15:40,439
我们什么都没了
We've nothing saved.

280
00:15:40,549 --> 00:15:42,480
别担心，我们会想到有的
Don't worry. I will think of something.

281
00:16:14,127 --> 00:16:16,127
又是这样
And again.

282
00:16:16,137 --> 00:16:17,958
又输了
This is a rout.

283
00:16:19,458 --> 00:16:21,989
我要不要仁慈点呢？
Shall I be merciful?

284
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,790
还是不要
I think not.

285
00:16:36,762 --> 00:16:38,542
你该怎么还我的债呢？
How will you pay your debt?

286
00:16:43,033 --> 00:16:45,394
我的就是你的
All that I have is already yours.

287
00:16:46,094 --> 00:16:47,615
还能给你什么呢？
What else can I give you?

288
00:16:48,005 --> 00:16:49,825
别再离开我
Don't leave me again.

289
00:16:50,405 --> 00:16:51,845
我从没有离开过你
I never left you.

290
00:17:15,051 --> 00:17:17,551
人们都无聊疯了
The men are going mad from boredom.

291
00:17:17,811 --> 00:17:20,862
今天我不得不割下一个骁勇的战士的双手因为他
Just today I had to cut the hands off a perfectly good Legionary

292
00:17:20,906 --> 00:17:22,931
杀害了一个平民
for murdering a civilian.

293
00:17:23,563 --> 00:17:28,374
接着 又得听一个不知道哪里来的自由民
Then I had to listen to a jumped up freedman

294
00:17:28,384 --> 00:17:29,504
胡说八道了半天
raving for hours

295
00:17:29,584 --> 00:17:34,765
说有个百夫长在勾引他的女儿
about one of my centurions seducing his daughters.

296
00:17:36,085 --> 00:17:38,446
听起来无聊死了
 It all sounds very tedious.  It is your uncle's fault.

297
00:17:38,486 --> 00:17:39,946
都是你舅舅的错
He should've taken the legions south after Pompey.

298
00:17:40,026 --> 00:17:42,247
他应该领兵南下

299
00:17:42,357 --> 00:17:43,557
追击庞贝
The men know it, and it makes them restless.

300
