你不就叫我订了50只猪嘛
50 pigs you have as ordered.

493
00:28:18,311 --> 00:28:21,461
你给了我50只病猪
50 diseased and scrofulous pigs.

494
00:28:21,802 --> 00:28:24,932
 其中有一只知道怎么去找蘑菇吃的  狡猾的畜生
 And one knows how to find truffles.  Tricky beasts.

495
00:28:24,962 --> 00:28:26,803
他们没吃橡树果吗？
Haven't been eating acorns, have they?

496
00:28:26,803 --> 00:28:28,103
去他妈的蘑菇，太多的橡树果了
Fucks them for truffling, too much acorns.

497
00:28:28,823 --> 00:28:31,364
我可以还你1/4的钱，出于我们的友谊
I will give you one quarter price. Out of friendship.

498
00:28:31,694 --> 00:28:35,305
你一个子儿都别想少，你这个胡子拉扎的奸贼
You'll give me every mumping denarius

499
00:28:35,355 --> 00:28:35,875
真的
 you cac-faced cunny!  Really,

500
00:28:35,875 --> 00:28:37,805
让我们不要用野蛮来解决问题
there is no call for rudeness.

501
00:28:37,805 --> 00:28:40,516
我听说印度人死了以后生命不灭？真的吗？
I'm told Hindus live on after death. Is that true?

502
00:28:40,546 --> 00:28:43,637
我们死了也会腐化，跟你们一样
Our bodies die and decay as yours will.

503
00:28:43,657 --> 00:28:45,947
但是我们的灵魂永生
But our souls live on eternally.

504
00:28:46,497 --> 00:28:47,617
嗯，那样的安排不错
Well, that's nice arrangements.

505
00:28:47,777 --> 00:28:49,808
 那么你就是不怕死咯？ 一点都不怕
 You're not afraid to die then?  Not at all.

